    <entry>
        <title type="html"><![CDATA[Better file sizes in Explorer details 1.4.2]]></title>
        <id>https://windhawk.net/mods/explorer-details-better-file-sizes#319700c1152b5e0d664b6832eff4bb003d92dfee</id>
        <link href="https://windhawk.net/mods/explorer-details-better-file-sizes"/>
        <updated>2024-11-09T15:24:43.000Z</updated>
        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<ul>
<li>Fixed the mod interfering with file size calculation in operations such as copying folders.</li>
<li>Added a workaround to the error message that says "Runtime Error - Not Enough space for thread Data". The error could occur when a process is shutting down due to a somewhat specific incompatibility between the Microsoft C++ runtime library and Windhawk's C++ library. It's not really harmful, as the process is shutting down anyway, but it can be annoying.</li>
</ul>]]></content>
        <author>
            <name>m417z</name>
            <uri>https://github.com/m417z</uri>
        </author>
